          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Ionization chambers filled with P10 gas (10%",
                "methane, 90% argon) and containing several tens of",
                "parallel plate electrodes on which the actinides sample",
                "was deposited. For fission fragments detection."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron detector was manufactured by",
                "Cryos-Beta and consists of an organic crystal of doped",
                "p-terphenyl C(18)H(14) coupled to a photomultiplier",
                "Photonis XP53X2). The crystal is a cylinder of 75 mm",
                "diameter, 500 mm length,  density of 1.23 g/cm3.",
                "The energy resolution of the detector was determined",
                "using gamma-sources in an energy range from 59.5 to",
                "1836 keV. For 137Cs (662 keV) about 10% (FWHM) was",
                "obtained. The energy calibration for gamma-rays was",
                "carried out by using the gamma-sources mentioned.",
                "Energy calibration for neutrons the detector was",
                "irradiated with spontaneous fission neutrons from",
                "a 252Cf source. A TOF spectrum was recorded and",
                "converted into energy.",
                "The total neutron efficiency consists of two",
                "components:",
                " a) the geometric acceptance corresponding to the solid",
                "angle - (2.73+-0.29)*10**-4,",
                " b) an intrinsic component, which is a function of the",
                "detected neutron energy, was determined by a PFNS",
                "measurement by using a point-like 252Cf(SF) source.",
                "The para-terphenyl detector (sensitive to neutrons and",
                "gamma-rays) was placed at a distance of about 1 m from",
                "the fission chamber perpendicular to the ion beam axis."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
